The paper deals with the stable matching problem, which is a classic problem in both computer science and economics. The paper focuses on the computational complexity of the problem when the preference lists are represented in a succinct way. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes subquadratic algorithms for finding and verifying stable matchings in specific models, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper analyzes the computational complexity of the problem for large values of d, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
